SIMPLE: greenness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greenness
<hw>Green"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>gr⟦emac⟧nnes</ets>.
See <er>Green.</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being green;
viridity; verdancy; <as>as, the <ex>greenness</ex> of grass, or of a
meadow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Freshness; vigor; newness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Immaturity; unripeness; <as>as, the
<ex>greenness</ex> of fruit</as>; inexperience; <as>as, the
<ex>greenness</ex> of youth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greenockite</ent>⟦br⟧
